<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="144" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,920,1306]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[253,339,1244,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Aufidus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,339,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Aufidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a really large distribution area that stretches from Java to the 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1209,1244,1270]" name="Samoa" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Samoa</collectingCountry>
islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Lallemand, V." pageId="1" pageNumber="144" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref6927" refString="Lallemand, V. (1949) Revision des Cercopinae (Hemiptera Homoptera) Premiere partie. Memoires de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Series 2, 32, 1 - 193." type="journal article" year="1949">Lallemand 1949</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
